node.description:
Yeezy added a new colorway to their Boost 380 product line with the adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Mist Reflective, now available on StockX. This model was originally known to be the Yeezy Boost 350 V3, but upon release it was given its own silhouette name. The mist colorway released in both reflective and non-reflective variations.

This 380 Mist Reflective features a reflective Mist Primeknit pattern on its upper and lacks the traditional lateral side stripe. An upgraded translucent Boost midsole and engineered gum outsole grip complete the design. These sneakers released in February of 2020 and retailed for $250.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur Kids is a futuristic, one-piece design that comes in a lighter Sulfur colorway and is constructed out of lightweight EVA and harvested algae.

The monochromatic shoe features oval and circular perforations for aeration during the summer heat, including a defined rubber tread for additional stability and in-sole support. The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur Kids footwear is slightly brighter than the previous Ochre and Desert Sand colorways.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur Kids’ earthy tone color palette footwear was released in April 2022, retailing at $65.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Infant) is part of the Yeezy Boost 350 collection that was created in collaboration with Kanye West and adidas. The sneaker comes in a Citrin colorway and was designed specifically for infants.

The upper of this Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Infant) has a sock-like construction that provides a snug and comfortable fit for infants. The upper also features a translucent stripe that is made of semi-transparent monofilament yarn, which allows some light to pass through. The midsole is made of adidas’ Boost technology, which provides excellent cushioning and energy return. The sole is made of rubber and provides excellent traction on various surfaces. This ensures that infants can walk and run with ease without the risk of slipping. The shoe also has a lace-up closure that allows for a secure fit.

What we love about the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Infant) is undoubtedly its 3D knit upper. The knit material is soft, lightweight, and breathable, ensuring that infant feet stay comfortable throughout the day. The shoe was released on September 23rd, 2019, at a retail price of $140.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand Kids is a result of a collaboration between adidas and Yeezy. The shoes were designed by popular musician Kanye West, who owns the Yeezy brand. This is not the first project the two brands have collaborated on.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand Kids was released in adult, kids' and infant sizing in the 'desert sand' colour scheme. They have been constructed using harvested algae and EVA, which gives the shoe its futuristic design and makes it lightweight.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand Kids was released on 11th June 2022 at a retail price of $208.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Reflective) features a reflective Citrin Primeknit upper with a mesh side stripe and textile heel tab. At the base, a Boost cushioned sole adds the finishing touch.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Reflective) released in September of 2019 and retailed for $220.

The summer of 2019 started with yet another regional Yeezy release, featuring the Synth Yeezy Boost 350 V2. Following successful regional releases of the Clay, Trfrm, and Hyperspace colorways, the Synth released exclusively in Africa, Asia, the Middle East, and Australia alongside the Antlia 350s in Europe.

This V2 sports more muted, neutral tones than previous colorways, features a nude Primeknit upper, a gum sole, the removal of the traditional heel tab, and the signature translucent side stripe. This particular adidas Yeezy sneaker retailed for $220.

The adidas Yeezy Powerphase Clear Brown was designed by Kanye West as part of a continued collaboration with adidas.

The shoe is primarily brown with a leather and suede upper featuring perforated detailing on the side in the same pattern as the three stripes synonymous with adidas, as well as the adidas logo and "Calabasas" branding in Gold Foil. It has a rubber outsole which features some stitching detail on the front and back plus more adidas branding on the base of the heel.

The adidas Yeezy Powerphase Clear Brown was first made available for retail at the price of $120 on September 18, 2019.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Kids was made available as part of the adidas's partnership with Yeezy, formerly known as Kanye West. This Yeezy Boost 350 V2 release arrives in a Cloud White/Cloud White/Cloud White colorway.

The adidas innovative Boost technology is used to design the midsole of this kids’ sneaker. The shoe's upper is designed by weaving a monofilament side stripe to reveal its re-engineered Primeknit. Shades of bluish-white and cream work together to form the sneaker's design featuring a fluffy cloud. In the meantime, blue-and-white patterns are outlined on one side of the shoe, and the other displays a transparent strip.

Something our experts think is the standout feature of the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Kids is the versatile, white-based colorway. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Kids was released at a retail price of $160 on September 21st, 2019.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Reflective) features a reflective Yeshaya Primeknit upper with a translucent mesh side stripe. From there, a cushioned Boost sole completes the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Reflective) released in January of 2020 and retailed for $250.

The adidas Yeezy 500 High Frosted Blue arrives with a molded upper composed of tonal blue suede, premium leather, and elastane. Off-white suede overlays cover the toe wrap and eyestay while elastane padding makes up the collar of the shoe for additional comfort. An off-white adiprene sole provides traction and stability, a fitting way to wrap up this hiking-inspired silhouette.

The adidas Yeezy 500 High Frosted Blue released in April of 2021 and retailed for $200.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin Kids is a collaboration between adidas and Kanye West.

The Citrin adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 for Kids comes in an all-Citrin color palette. The upper is built with a mixture of PrimeKnit material and translucent monofilament mesh, offering lightweight feel and improved breathability. The shoe features adidas' Boost cushioning technology, which provides comfort and responsiveness. The midsole is made of semi-translucent TPU material. In addition, this model of sneaker features a pull tab on the heel for easy on-and-off wear. The shoe also includes a durable rubber outsole with patterned traction for grip and sturdiness.

What we think is the best feature of these sneakers is their sleek and modern design. These shoes feature a PrimeKnit upper in a soft and neutral Citrin colorway, which gives them a versatile and stylish look. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin Kids was released on September 23rd, 2019, and sold for a recommended retail price of about $160.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx Reflective is a part of the adidas Yeezy Boost series, designed in collaboration between adidas and very notable figure, Kanye West.

The Yeezy adidas Boost 380 Onyx Reflective upper is composed of a semi-translucent woven material and is engineered using Primeknit technology for flexibility. The shoe features reflective detailing and has a rubber sole that is made from adidas' patented Boost technology. The sneaker is designed with an onyx colorway and black and round races. The shoe also features a sock-like fit, with a distinctive pattern throughout the upper.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx Reflective were released on November 27, 2020 at a retail price of $250.

The "adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon (Kids)" was launched as part of the kids’ sports collection of the adidas Brand.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon Kids is made from Primeknit/ knitted fabric material at the upper part and synthetic yarn at the soles. The sneaker comes with a Zyon color at the upper and white at the soles. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon Kids features elastic shoelaces placed on the non-metallic eyelets.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon (Kids) became available on July 18th, 2020 at a retail price of $160.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Triple Black is the outcome of the collaboration between adidas and Kanye West's fashion brand - Yeezy.

The Triple Black adidas Yeezy Boost 750 sneaker features an all-black colorway with a suede upper. The suede upper also features a mid-foot strap, offering additional lockdown support for a secure fit. At the same time, its Boost midsole, made of adidas' Boost technology ensures cushioning and comfort. The design is completed by the treaded rubber outsole for traction.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Triple Black was released on December 19th, 2015 and it retailed at $350.

Yeezy adds to its ever growing 700 line with the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Carbon Blue, now available on StockX. Trailing the releases of the Magnet and Teal Blue colorways, this shoe stays true to the Yeezy aesthetic with a new tonal variation that stays in the same ballpark of other 700 releases.

This 700 is composed of a mix of grey and carbon blue tones that are assorted amongst a mix of suede and mesh. A grey rubber midsole and gum outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 for $300.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur (Infants) is a slip-on sandal that was released by adidas in collaboration with Kanye West’s Yeezy brand as the 11th product line from the adidas Yeezy brand.

The adidas Yeezy Foam runners feature a monochromatic tan appearance labeled as the Sulfur colorway which resembles a yellowish beige hue. They are made from EVA foam using a single-piece foam injection molding technique, which also gives them a sculpted appearance. The sculpted appearance is further enhanced by oval cut openings on the side walls. These work hand in hand with strategically placed vents to help with breathability and keep the foot cool.

One thing we love about the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur (Infants) is the foam material used in construction. It gives the shoe a lightweight, flexible feel, making it comfortable for all-day use. The infant-sized shoes were released for retail on the 6th of April 2022, with a retail price of $45.

Yeezy expands its 700 color pallette once again with the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 "Magnet", now available on StockX. Despite an existing line of Yeezy 700s assorted in six colorways, the Magnet is the first time this colorway has been used.

This 700 features a grey upper with suede overlays and orange accents on the midsole. Its chunky midsole is inspired by the Adidas KB3 atop a gum outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in September of 2019 and retailed for $300.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper Reflective is part of the original Yeezy Boost 380 line created by adidas in collaboration with Kanye West.

The Pepper adidas Yeezy Boost 380 has an upper that is constructed from premium materials to provide durability. The Primeknit textile used on the upper is both breathable and stretchable to mold to the foot. The sneaker features reflective detailing and comes in a Pepper colorway with beige laces. The sneaker is also equipped with adidas' signature Boost technology and has a gum-like translucent rubber outsole with a herringbone pattern.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Pepper Reflective was released on September 11, 2020 at a retail price of $250.

Yeezy introduced a new colorway to their 700 MNVN series with the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange, now available on StockX. Although the silhouette is similar to previous models, this shoe differs by displaying "700" branding on the upper using compact materials.

This Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN is comprised of an orange nylon upper paired with reflective detailing. A solid black sole with Boost cushioning completes the design. These sneakers released in February of 2020 and retailed for $220.

While soldiers rave about the seven core Army values, the sneaker community can go off about the adidas Yeezy Boost V2 350 Core Green. Setting a battlefield tone, this silhouette comes with a core black upper and sole. They also feature core black "SPLY-350" branding across a core green stripe on both sides. These dropped in November 2016 and retailed at $220. Dont be afraid to break rank and place a Bid on StockX.

The adidas Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas Core White was part of a collaboration between rapper Kanye West and adidas. It draws its inspiration from the 80s with an Off-White buttery leather design throughout.

The Yeezy Powerphase features a premium off-white leather upper with perforated 3-Stripes, gold foil Calabasas branding on the lateral side, and an adidas wordmark on the eye stay logo window. The sneaker arrives in an all white colorway with a matching rubber sole and matching laces.

The adidas Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas Core White was originally released on the 28th of March 2017 for an initial retail price of $120.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White Kids is a highly sought-after sneaker that was released on March 6, 2021. This shoe features a unique design that is sure to turn heads, with a white knit upper that is both breathable and comfortable. The shoe also features a unique lacing system that provides a secure fit, as well as a durable rubber outsole that provides excellent traction. The adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White Kids is made from high-quality materials, ensuring that it will last for years to come. This sneaker is available at a retail price of $140, making it an affordable option for parents looking for a stylish and comfortable shoe for their kids. Don't miss out on this must-have sneaker for your little ones!

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock is a part of the adidas Yeezy Boost line, which is a series of sneakers created by adidas in collaboration with rapper and fashion designer Kanye West.

The Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock has outsoles that are made from rubber material and insoles that are designed using adidas' Boost technology, which uses a foam sole to provide cushioning. The upper and laces are made of a single-piece Primeknit material. The Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock is available in a grayish-brown "moonrock" colorway, which features contrasting dark gray stitching and a translucent outsole.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock was released on November 14, 2015 at a retail price of $200.

In continuation of its ever growing 700 line, Yeezy brand keeps it simple with the Adidas Yeezy Boost 700 "Teal Blue", now available on StockX. Trailing the releases of the Magnet and Inertia colorways, this shoe stays true to the Yeezy aesthetic with a new tonal variation that stays in the same ballpark of other 700 releases.
This 700 is composed of a mix of grey and teal tones that are assorted amongst a mix of suede and mesh. A grey rubber midsole and gum outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in October of 2019 for $300.

Hope you're ready to smash open that piggy bank and spend some pennies on the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Copper. Displaying a rich look, these have a core black upper and sole. There's also core black "SPLY-350" branding across the core copper stripe on both sides. These dropped in November 2016 and retailed at $220, Add more sauce to your sneaker collection on StockX.

With simple designs and a color scheme of two-tone shades, the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Cream Clay (I) generally emphasizes a minimalist look. 

The top, which is constructed of a combination of lightweight EVA, has a base color of cream with brown and cream splashes that look as if they were painted on with a brush. Flowing lines and numerous punched holes for amphibious wear distinguish the distinctive silhouette. With a slip-on design and an elasticized collar that provides a snug fit and simple on/off functionality, the Yeezy Foam RNNR is intended to be worn without laces.

What we think is the notable feature of this slip-on infant shoe is the use of sustainable materials in its design. The upper is made from an algae-based foam material, contributing to eco-friendly manufacturing practices. The adidas Yeezy foam RNNR MX Cream Clay (I) was released on 2nd August 2021 and retailed at the price of $40.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand Infants is one of the offerings from the Yeezy Foam Runner collection designed by rapper Kanye West.

The shoe comes in a neutral beige color, with a detailed structure molded in one piece. The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand Infants has cut-outs that offer ventilation and complete the design. Completely made of an algae-based foam, this shoe springs when you take a step. The wave-like traction pattern on the sole provides grip and durability for regular life activities.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand Infant version was made available on 11 June 2022, retailing at $45.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Resin Kids is a kids’-exclusive slip-on shoe from the adidas Yeezy Slide lineup in a Resin colorway.

Constructed with injected EVA foam, this slip-on shoe features a single-strap upper dressed in a monochromatic Resin hue. Plush cushioning is used on the footbed for comfort. Minimal branding details are featured on this Yeezy slide with the adidas Three Stripes debossed on the footbed. Rounding out this shoe’s design is an outsole with a series of strategically placed flex grooves for traction. 

What our experts love about this Yeezy slide is its design and comfort. The injected EVA foam provides lightweight durability, while the footbed cushioning provides comfort. Strategic flex groove placement on the outsole offers optimal traction and comfort. The versatile Light Green Resin colorway gives this slip-on shoe a unique and eye-catching look. The adidas Yeezy Slide Resin Kids was released on December 6th, 2019, for a retail price of $45.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Light Grey Glow In the Dark is a high-level glowing-in-the-dark sneaker. The glowing sneakers detail a light grey patent leather elevated with a flexible mid-foot band.

Since its release in the market, the adidas Yeezy Boost 750 has gained a lot of profit because of its flexible, absorbent, comfortable, and athletic quality. The glowing sneakers have round rope shoe laces, come in light grey, and are made from a foam material.

The Yeezy Boost 750 Light Grey Glow In the Dark released on November 6, 2016 at a price of $350.

node.description:
The adidas Yeezy Powerphase Simple Brown is one of the adidas Yeezy Powerphase sneakers featuring a Simple Brown color throughout.

The adidas Yeezy Powerphase Simple Brown sneaker’s design is inspired by Kanye West’s preference for earth-toned shoes, a common theme in his adidas Yeezy line. The sneaker’s entire upper appears in light brown suede, including the perforated midpanel, the toe, the heel, and the signature three stripes. The color scheme is contrasted with the visible Calabasas detailing in gold foil on the outer side of the sneaker and the green embroidered adidas branding next to the eyelets, a mesh sock liner, and laces. Completing the design is the brown treaded rubber sole for cushioning and traction.

The adidas Yeezy Powerphase Simple Brown debuted on September 18th, 2019, with a retail price of $120.

Yeezy added a new colorway to their 700 MNVN series with the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone, now available on StockX. Although the silhouette dons a familiar Boost 700 sole, this shoe differs by displaying "700" branding on the upper using compact materials. 

This Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN is comprised of a Bone nylon upper paired with reflective detailing. A solid black sole with Boost cushioning completes the design. These sneakers released in April of 2020 and retailed for $220.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner Solid Grey Kids was released to improve Yeezy's sleek minimal aesthetic design and deliver a chunky signature, in a kids’ shoe. The sneaker comes in a Solid Grey/Chalk White/Core Black colorway.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner Solid Grey Kids displays a layered upper crafted with nubuck and leather. Also, the shoe displays a collar and mid-panel with solid gray mesh. The quarter panel, forefoot, and mid-panel house contrasting black-hued patterns. Furthermore, this kids’ sneaker showcases a Boost unit affixed to the midsole to deliver cushioning, while a patterned herringbone on the outsole provides traction.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner Solid Grey Kids was released on August 17th, 2017, at a retail price of $180.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate (Kids) is a kids' iteration of the avant-garde design of the Yeezy 450. Crafted from knit, these Dark Slate sneakers feature a black colorway from top to bottom.

The Yeezy 450 for kids takes on a dark slate colorway in comparison to the popular Cloud White Yeezys. A heavily knit upper class in Dark Slate lines up the 40 Dark Slate Kids cagey design. The ankle entry features a sock-like construction for a snug fit around your foot. Rope laces, still taking on the black color, secure the fit while an EVA midsole creeps up from the underfoot to deliver cushioning. An adidas logo under the wavy outsole signs off the subdued aesthetic of these Kanye West-inspired kicks.

What is the standout feature of the sneaker? As our experts state, it is the quirky design that takes on a dark slate colorway for a subdued yet eye-catching aesthetic. These kicks are a must-have for kids foraying into the world of high fashion. The adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate (Kids) was released on June 26, 2021, retailing for $140.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black 2015 comes dressed primarily in a Pirate Black color scheme with small accents of dark gray and red.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon Infants comes in a Zyon color scheme.

The sneaker also features a zig-zag pattern on the Primeknit upper. The midsole incorporates adidas' signature Boost cushioning technology, which provides cushioning and responsiveness and ensures extra comfort and support. The outsole is composed of a durable rubber compound that provides grip and stability.

One notable feature of the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon Infants is its colorway. The shoe showcases a blend of earthy and neutral tones, including shades of grey, beige, and brown. This color palette creates a versatile and fashionable look. The infants’ sizing of the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon was released on July 18, 2020, and originally sold for a retail price of $140.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Bone (I) is a footwear option for infants that was released as part of the Yeezy brand by Kanye West.

The outsole of the Yeezy Slide Bone Infants is made of the same foam material as the rest of the slide, with a series of grooves strategically placed for added grip and stability.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Bone (I) was released on December 6th, 2019 at a retail price of $35.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay (Kids) is a preschool edition sneaker from the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 collaborative sneaker lineup in a ‘Clay’ colorway.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (Infant) is a Yeezy Boost 350 model sneaker that was designed for infants.

The Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (Infant) comes in a blend of colors, including Pirate Black, Blue Gray, and Core Black. The midsole is designed with adidas' exclusive Boost technology, which is known for its responsiveness and cushioning properties. The outsole is made from a durable rubber material that provides excellent traction, ensuring that your infant has a firm grip on the ground when walking or running. The sole is lightweight, which makes it comfortable for your little one to wear for extended periods. The stretchy laces also ensure that the shoe fits snugly around your infant's foot.

We think that the standout feature of the shoe is the prime-knit upper construction, which provides excellent breathability and a snug fit around the infant's foot. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (Infant) was released on August 27th, 2016, at a retail price of $130.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Resin (Infants) is part of the Yeezy line, which is a collaboration between adidas and the rapper Kanye West. It was designed specifically for babies and toddlers.

The Yeezy Slide Resin for infants has an all-Resin colorway and a slip-on design, ensuring that parents can get them onto the feet of their infants with ease. The slide has a cushioned footbed that provides ample support for the baby’s sensitive feet. The outsole is made with high-quality rubber, providing a sturdy grip and durability for infants learning to walk.

We think that the outstanding feature of the adidas Yeezy Slide Resin is its construction. The slide is made with a durable and lightweight resin upper that is easy to clean and maintain, making it perfect for kids who are always on the go. The adidas Yeezy Slide Resin (Infants) was released on December 6th, 2019, at a retail price of $35.

Yeezy added to their glow-in-the-dark catalog by releasing a new colorway of the 380 with the Yeezy Boost 380 Hylte Glow. This is the second time in 2020 that Yeezy added glow-in-the-dark attributes to a 380, the first being the Yeezy Boost 380 Calcite that was released earlier in the fall.

The Yeezy Boost 380 Hylte Glow features a tonal yellow camo-print Primeknit upper with a flat neon green side spot. In typical Yeezy fashion, a dark grey translucent Boost sole and rope laces gear this release for daily wear.

The Yeezy Boost 380 Hylte Glow released in December of 2020 and retailed for $230.

Released in 2015, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtle Dove is the first colorway to kick off Yeezy's expansive 350 line. Composed of a grey and brown patterned Primeknit, the design was one of the most comfort focus Yeezy designs at the time and still is to this day. At the base, a grooved Boost outsole delivers adidas' renowned cushioning.

To shop the latest 2022 re-issue, click here.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Sand Grey (Kids) feature injected EVA foam and part-harvested algae for a lightweight build on the slip-on. The silhouette is dressed in a swirl of earth-toned colors for this iteration.

The flexible Yeezy slides flaunt ventilation ports on the sides as well as the vamp on the forefoot. Coral accents decorate the MX Sand Grey colorway on the silhouette. Featuring a Cloud White color scheme, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Infant is a specific variation of adidas' Yeezy Boost 350 V2 sneakers appearing in infant sizing.    

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Infant is made of a multicolored, re-engineered Primeknit upper. Its upper design also incorporates a woven side stripe made of post-dyed monofilament. Completing the upper design is the shoe's lacing system to ensure a comfortable and adjustable fitting. The sneaker's lower design features a BOOST sole unit that features adidas BOOST technology. BOOST midsole provides comfort through cushioning and impact absorption, while the outer treads optimize traction on various surfaces.

What we love about this adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Infant that first appeared on the market on September 21, 2019 with a retail price of $140 is the PrimeKnit upper that makes it light and allows unrestricted airflow during wear.

Yeezy applied the pressure during the 2020 holiday season and released another 380 colorway with the Yeezy Boost 380 Lmnte. This release follows Yeezy’s reputation of earth-toned colorways, balancing dark and light tones throughout the silhouette, similar to the look of fallen leaves on the forest floor.

The Yeezy Boost 380 Lmnte is composed of a tonal brown camo-print Primeknit upper with a golden spot on the lateral foot. A dark grey translucent Boost midsole, golden yellow outsole, and rope laces channel hiking boot vibes, while retaining the comfortable runner identity that the 380 is known for.

The Yeezy Boost 380 Lmnte released in December of 2020 and retailed for $230.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Kids) is a unique addition to the Yeezy line, reimagining the classic slide design with an infusion of Kanye West's signature avant-garde aesthetics.

The Enflame Orange Yeezy slides come in a Vibrant Orange hue, which immediately makes them stand out. The monochromatic orange covers the entire slide, including the strap and underneath the footbed, showcasing a blend of minimalist design with flair. The slides are made from a foam material, which keeps them lightweight and ensures maximum comfort during wear. This is further helped by the footbed, which conforms to the shape of the foot allowing for a snug fit.

What we love most about the adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Kids) is the outsole, which has aggressive contour lines to maximize grip and traction, helping to prevent the foot from sliding around. The kids-sized shoe was released for retail on June 21st, 2021, priced at $45.

You can never have too much heat, so cop the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black. This Yeezy Boost 350 V2 comes with a black upper, black midsole, and a black sole. These sneakers released in June 2019 and retailed for $220. Buy these today on StockX. Also available in adult sizing.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mineral Blue (Infants) is an infant's size sneaker that was released as a collaboration between adidas and artist Kanye West.

The Yeezy Foam RNNR in Mineral Blue for infants has a Mineral Blue colorway and features a design that allows for easy on-and-off access. The shoe features a textured sole that provides traction for little ones who are beginning to explore their surroundings. The foam material is also incredibly lightweight, making it easy for children to move around without any added weight or discomfort.

Our experts say that the standout feature of the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mineral Blue (Infants) is its unique foam material that covers the entire shoe. This foam is a trademark technology from adidas that also adds a layer of cushioning to the shoe, providing a comfortable and lightweight feel for the infant. The material and Mineral Blue colorway make this shoe perfect for both boys and girls. The shoe was released on May 29th, 2021 at a retail price of $40.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Reflective) features a triple-Antlia Primeknit upper, with the Antlia palette taking on a soft yellow hue that is shot through with the typical gray seen on many Boost 350 V2 models. From there, the iconic "three stripes" of adidas cover the inner heel of the shoe, and "Boost" technology in a Gum-colored heel complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Reflective) released in June of 2019 and retailed for $220

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light (Infant) is a highly sought-after sneaker created through a collaboration between adidas and Kanye West, the American rapper, and fashion designer.

The shoe features a distinctive upper crafted using PrimeKnit material, which is lightweight and breathable, offering a comfortable snug fit. It has cream as the predominant color which also extends to the sole unit. This Yeezy Boost 350 V2 retains some of the signature design elements of the silhouette like the distinctive stripe pattern on the side, and the iconic "SPLY-350" text on the lateral side.

One thing our experts love about the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light (Infant) is the incorporation of Boost technology into the midsole. This helps with cushioning the foot, while also providing impact absorption which helps to enhance a comfortable experience for everyday wear. The infant-sized shoes were first released for retail in August 2021 for $140 retail.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Bone (K) is dressed in an all-bone hue. The slip-on shoe is made of injected EVA foam and has a neutral ivory finish.

The open-toe, breezy design of the slide and the soft top layer of the footbed are the distinguishing characteristics of this Bone Yeezy Slide for kids. Only the adidas 3-Stripes logo, which is imprinted at the heel of the footbed, is used as exterior branding on these bone-colored shoes. The outsole of the slip-on design has strategically placed grooves and good traction. The shoe also has a top soft layer in its footbed.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Bone (K) was launched on December 6, 2019, with a suggested market price of $45.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Sand Grey (Infants) is a collaboration between adidas and Kanye West. The shoe was specifically designed for infants and features an MX Sand Gray colorway.

The Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Sand Gray (Infants) is made from a special foam material that is both lightweight and durable. The shoe features a perforated design with large openings. The sole incorporates a single piece of foam material that runs the entire length of the shoe. The foam material is soft and lightweight, providing cushioning and shock absorption for the feet.

We believe that the standout feature of the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Sand Grey (Infants) is its unique slip-on design. Unlike traditional sneakers that require lacing, Velcro, or buckles to secure them to the feet, the Foam RNNR MX Sand Gray simply slides onto the foot like a sock. This makes it incredibly easy and convenient to put on and take off, which is especially useful for parents of young children. The shoe was released on December 11th, 2021, at a retail price of $40.

The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah (Infant) is part of the Yeezy Boost series created by adidas in collaboration with rapper Kanye West.

The Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah for infants comes in an Alvah colorway. Underfoot, the sneaker features a full-length EVA midsole that provides cushioning and support for little feet. The midsole is designed to absorb shock and reduce impact, reducing the risk of injuries. The outsole is constructed using lightweight rubber that provides additional traction and durability. The lacing system integrates seamlessly with the upper, providing a locked-in feel that is ideal for active children.

We think that the standout feature of the adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah (Infant) is its design. The shoe features a lightweight and breathable upper made of a two-layer mesh material that is both durable and comfortable. The upper also incorporates an RPU cage that wraps around the midfoot, providing additional support and stability. The shoe was released on April 11th, 2020 at a retail price of $140.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate Infant is a highly sought-after sneaker that boasts a unique design and premium materials. Released on June 26, 2021, this shoe features a dark slate colorway that adds a touch of sophistication to any outfit. The upper is made of a breathable mesh material that provides comfort and durability, while the sole is crafted from adidas' signature Boost technology for superior cushioning and support. The shoe also features a laceless design that adds to its sleek and modern aesthetic. With a retail price of $120, the adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate Infant is a must-have for any sneaker enthusiast looking for a stylish and comfortable shoe.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Red (Kids) opts for premium materials that infuse Kanye West's styling into the comfort-oriented sneakers. These Yeezys adopt a Prime knit upper finished in black and red accents.

Employing Yeezy 350 construction, the upper is draped in black with contrast-hued fibers across the yarn working to elicit a speckled effect. The translucent rubber midsole also takes on dark hues in line with the blacked-out motif of the darkest V2. What our experts like about the Yeezy Boost V2 Black Red is the minimalistic design that allows Adidas to focus on the comfort offerings. The Boost midsole aids in this cause. adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Red (Kids) was released on December 5, 2020, retailing for $160.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mineral Blue (Kids) comes in an all-Mineral Blue color scheme.

The Mineral Blue adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR for kids features an upper made from a single piece of foam compound, which offers a lightweight feel and comfort. The shoe's midsole is crafted of EVA foam, providing cushioning and impact absorption. In addition, the outsole features deep grooves and a wavy pattern that provide sturdiness and traction.

What we love about the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mineral Blue is its futuristic and sleek silhouette, and a slip-on construction and seamless one-piece upper, creating a minimalist and modern look. The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mineral Blue (Kids) was released on May 29th, 2021, and sold for a retail price of $60.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat Reflective arrives in an all-blue oat color scheme.

The shoe features a sock-like construction for a snug and secure fit. The sneaker's lacing system ensures a customizable fit. The shoe's midsole features adidas' signature Boost technology, which provides cushioning and energy return while offering responsiveness and comfort. The sneaker has an outsole crafted with a durable rubber compound, providing grip and traction.

The standout feature of the adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat Reflective is its reflective elements. These sneakers feature reflective detailing on the upper, which illuminates when exposed to light. This unique characteristic adds a captivating and futuristic touch to the design. The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 was released on July 24th, 2020, and sold for a retail price of $250.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light Kids is a highly sought-after sneaker that combines style and comfort. This shoe features a light-toned Primeknit upper with a translucent stripe, providing a sleek and modern look. The Boost midsole technology offers superior cushioning and support, making it perfect for everyday wear. The release date for this shoe is August 28th, 2021, and it retails for $160. The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light Kids is made with high-quality materials, ensuring durability and longevity. This shoe is a must-have for any sneaker enthusiast looking for a stylish and comfortable option for their kids. Get your hands on this limited edition sneaker before it's too late!

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner (Infant) comes in a Solid Gray, Chalk White, and Core Black color palette.

The Wave Runner adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Grey for infants adopts a classic silhouette with an upper that is crafted with a mix of materials, including suede overlays, mesh panels, and synthetic leather elements, offering durability and breathability. The sneaker features adidas' Boost technology in the midsole, which provides responsive cushioning and impact reduction. The shoe's design is completed with a rubber outsole that provides stability and grip.

Our experts love the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner and its chunky and retro-inspired design. These sneakers feature a mix of gray, blue, and orange hues on the upper, creating a visually dynamic and stylish look. The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner (Infant) was released on August 17, 2019, and sold for a retail price of $150.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon (Infants) was released as a collaboration between Kanye West and adidas. The sneaker adopts the classic low-top Yeezy Boost silhouette in a Carbon colorway.

The shoe also incorporates a durable rubber outsole with a distinct tread pattern, offering traction and sturdiness.

What we love about this sneaker is its two-tone upper material, which creates an elegant and sophisticated look. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon (Infants) was released on October 2nd, 2020, and sold for a list price of $140.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Infants) designed for infants, is a comfortable sandal created in collaboration between Adidas and Kanye West's Yeezy brand. These infant sized Yeezy Slides come in a striking Enflame Orange colorway. The Yeezy branding is discreetly featured on the footbed.

The outsole of the adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Infants) is made of durable rubber material that provides traction and grip, even on smooth surfaces.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Infants) was available at a retail price of $35 when it was released on June 21st, 2021.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon (Kids) features a Primeknit upper with a mix of black and gray threads, creating a subtle look. The sneaker has a transparent stripe revealing a more cream-colored inner in place of the traditional SPLY-350 boost stripe.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark Reflective was released on 11th July 2019 with its retail price set at $250.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil (Infant) is part of a collaboration between adidas and Kanye West.

The adidas Yeezy Powerphase Quiet Grey was released in addition to the collaborative line between adidas and Kanye West's Yeezy brand. It takes inspiration from vintage athletic footwear.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya Infant is a highly sought-after sneaker that was released on January 25, 2020. This shoe features a sleek and stylish design that is perfect for infants. The upper is made of a breathable and durable Primeknit material that provides a comfortable fit. The shoe also features a Boost midsole that offers excellent cushioning and support. The Yeshaya colorway is a unique blend of white and grey that gives the shoe a clean and modern look. Last but not least, the shoe has a translucent side stripe in place of the standard SPLY-350 marking. The midsole uses ridged TPU sidewalls with semi-translucent characteristics, showing full-length adidas Boost cushioning inside, while integrated lacing allows for fit customization.

Something we love about the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Non-Reflective is the side stripe made of post-dyed monofilament woven into the top. The laces have reflective threads sewn into them. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black (I) Non-Reflective was released on 7th June 2019 and retailed at $140.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow (Infant) was released as part of Kanye West's Yeezy line. This shoe is designed specifically for infants and toddlers and comes in a Glow colorway.

The shoe's midsole is made of Boost technology, which provides cushioning and energy return, making it comfortable for little ones to walk, run, and play. The outsole is made of a durable rubber material that provides grip and traction on a variety of surfaces.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark (Infant), a flexible sneaker specifically sized for infants, has been designed in collaboration with Kanye West to create a comfortable, supportive, and highly fashionable baby shoe.

Add some major heat for your summer closet with the Air Fear Of God Moccasin Particle Beige. This Air FOG Moccasin comes with a beige upper, black Nike "Swoosh", sail midsole, and a translucent sole. These sneakers released in May 2019 and retailed for $170. Buy a pair on StockX today.

node.description:
The Nike Air Max 95 Naija is among the Nike Air Max 95 brands of shoes. It arrives in a combination of Pine Green, Black, Sub Lime and White

The Naija Nike Air Max 95 shoe’s upper design features a mini Swoosh that is dressed in Black next to the heel cap, a Black lacing system across the tongue in the same color, an "Air Max" on the two-colored tongue tag, and the Pine Green and Sublime panels on the sides. The shoe’s lower design features a Black rubber midsole with Air Max Units in Pine Green for cushioning and impact absorption and the treaded outsole for grip.

Something that our experts value about this Nike Air Max 95 Naija that made its debut on 28th September 2020, with a market retail price of $170 is its multicolored design. Besides making it attractive and stylish, this color design makes it unique among Nike’s brands of Air Max 95 sneakers.

The New Balance 327 Sea Salt Rust Oxide (Women's) upper features durable leather and breathable mesh material for comfort. The rubber outsole offers optimal traction, while the sock-like fit reinforces heel integrity.

The New Balance 327 Sea Salt Rust Oxide (W) has a 4mm drop and a lightweight upper for a quick, responsive feel. The sneaker also features enhanced dampness control for reduced risk of blistering, which also prevents moisture retention and increased breathability. The sneaker is available in women’s sizing.

The women’s New Balance 327 Sea Salt Rust Oxide (W) was released in March 2022 and retailed at $110.

In collaboration with Joe Freshgoods, the New Balance 2002R Joe Freshgoods Conversations Amongst Us draws inspiration from crucial dialogues that connect the Black community. It arrives with a neutral-toned upper constructed with nylon, leather, and premium suede. Hits of orange and yellow add a subtle contrast. On the insole, graphics of two figures conversing nod to the collection's theme of communication. From there, a cream and orange NERGY sole provides cushioning and support.

The New Balance 550 Joe Freshgoods Conversations Amongst Us released in April of 2022 and retailed for $130.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low Pixel Particle Beige (W) is a relaunch of Bruce Kilgore’s original 1982 design. The Particle Beige/black-white colorway is designed by applying a soft pink hue to the all-leather upper.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low Pixel Particle Beige (W) features an exaggerated heel tab and floating eyestay and is updated with a cut-out Swoosh. Furthermore, the low top of this Nike Air Force 1 sneaker rides on a contrasting white midsole that adds large, pixelated detailing for a distorted aesthetic. An Airsole unit gives you lightweight cushioning.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low Pixel Particle Beige (W) was made available on October 15, 2020, at a retail price of $100.

The New Balance 2002R Sweet Caramel is a retro-inspired running shoe from the New Balance 2002R lineup in a ‘Sweet Caramel’ colorway.

This shoe features an upper made of a Grey mesh base cut out with tonal leather and Sweet Caramel suede overlays, which dominate the upper. A Classic Grey ‘N’ logo with a White outline appears on both sides of the mid-panel, while ‘2002R’ branding features on the lateral collar. A Grey and White midsole with ABZORB cushioning in the heel and a Black N-ergy outsole complete the design.

The New Balance 2002R Sweet Caramel was released on May 11th, 2022, for a retail price of $120.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Particle Beige (W) arrives in a particle beige, black-metallic red bronze colorway.

The Jordan 1 Mid SE Particle Beige (W) dons the silhouette with an upper crafted from leather and suede materials. The sneaker's rubber outsole is both grippy and durable, while the EVA foam in the midsole offers lightweight comfort and padding. The shoe's toe box is perforated for breathability. The shoe features a black Nike Swoosh on the lateral sides, "Jumpman Air" on the tongue, and the Air Jordan logo on one side.

The women’s rendition of the Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Particle Beige (W) was released on April 23, 2021, and retailed for $125.

The New Balance 327 Calm Taupe Morning Fog W features breathable morning fog-colored nylon uppers and calm taupe suede overlays on the vamp, toebox, rear quarter, and eye stays. 

To create a contrast on the sneaker, its heel, and mudguard feature a light blue color scheme. The only branding is a giant white "N" logo on the lateral side, with the exception of a little "New Balance" tag printed on the mudguard. A white midsole that supports the gum outsole spanning from the toe to the heels completes its design.

The New Balance 327 Calm Taupe Morning Fog W was released on 15th February 2022. The women’s sneaker retailed at $110.

If you’re going for a "Man of the Woods" vibe this fall, the Air Jordan 3 JTH Bio Beige is a must cop. Inspired by Justin Timberlake’s 2018 album, and specifically the song "Higher Higher" this Jordan 3 is all about giving your fit an earth and woods feel. These 3s feature a Bio Beige suede upper, black on black elephant print overlays and the iconic Nike Air branding on the heels. Another additional detail are insoles that read "FAME IS A LIE" and "STRESS IS CRUEL." These special edition Justin Timberlake Jordans dropped in August of 2018 for $250. Don’t cry me a river, place a Bid on these today.

The New Balance 2002R White Beige is a beige low-top sneaker launched by New Balance.

The New Balance 2002R features a low-top paneled suede and mesh upper in tones of beige and white. The shoe’s trim is silver-tone throughout and has a tonal lace-up closure. For branding, the sneaker has a textile logo patch in silver tone on the padded tongue, a rubberized logo at the round toe, an embroidered logo at the vamp, and the tonal ‘N’ logo applique at the sides. The ABZORB foam rubber midsole provides superior cushioning and the treaded rubber outsole provides traction.

The New Balance 2002R White Beige was released on February 18th, 2021 with its retail price set at $160.

The New Balance 2002R Beige comes in a beige, beige, and silver color scheme.

The New Balance 2002R Beige has an upper that is crafted from beige fabric with overlays of beige suede. The mesh upper, including the tongue and heel, is accentuated with beige detailing. The midsole is a pure white color with subtle beige accents to provide contrast. The lacing system is completed with beige threads and New Balance emblems on the tongue. An "N" logo is displayed on the lateral sides. The outsole is constructed from durable rubber for grip.

The New Balance 2002R Beige was released for $160 on October 16th, 2021.

After being inspired by the Air Yeezy 2 colorway silhouette, Nike released the Nike Air Foamposite Pro Yeezy with a laser crimson colorway to give it a unique spin. The black/laser crimson colorway signature features carbon fiber prints on its upper.

The Air Foamposite Pro Yeezy is adorned with neon red accents with a black upper and a glow-in-the-dark outsole. It features crimson at the heel, liner, and tongue, with eyestays displaying a faux snakeskin pattern. Inspired by Kanye West's 2012 model, a black Foamposite shell and Swoosh team with a black mesh/nubuck upper to design the sneaker.

The Nike Air Foamposite Pro Yeezy was released at a retail price of $250 on April 19, 2014.

The Nike Air Max 1 Daisy features white uppers as well as a white sole. At the heel of the shoe, the signature Air unit, which absorbs shock and offers padding, can be seen in bright green. The sneaker features a black-and-white daisy pattern at the heel as well as a blue-and-white daisy pattern along the tongue. The laces are pale green, and a bright yellow fabric Swoosh is displayed on the sides of the shoes.

The Nike Air Max 1 Daisy released in June of 2020 and retailed for $140.

The Nike Air Presto Naija is a green-based colorway sneaker, that pays tribute to the stylish Nigerian kits for the Olympics. Just like the lively footballing spirit they embody, the Naija Air Prestos feature pine green, green strike, and black-white colorways to create iconic tribal patterns on the sneakers. Black "Naija" lettering on the back of the shoe and a semi-translucent TPU overlay with Nike Swoosh on the rubber midsole round off the aesthetically pleasing Naija Prestos similar to the TD design.

An air-cushioned sole and foam sole support the Nike Air Presto Naija making sure it’s lightweight and comfortable. Look closely and you’ll spot embellishments like the visible air cushioning and contrasting Nike branding, reflective accents, and lace loops.

What our experts love is that flex grooves ensure the Nike Air Naijas retain their track identity. The sneakers double up as off-track shoes as well. These Nike Air Presto Naija, released on September 28th, 2020 at $130, blend with the Nigerian football team kit or other Nike sportswear for a lively and chic look.

Dressed in Particle Beige/Particle Beige-Phantom colorway, the Nike Air Force 1 Sage Low Particle Beige W is one of Nike’s collections for women.

The Particle Beige W Nike Air Force 1 Sage Low features a white midsole with a slight wedge, and a light, beige-colored suede upper. The sneaker’s design also features a padded collar to optimize comfort, perforations on the toe box for breathability, a rubber outsole for traction, an iconic Nike Swoosh on the sides, and a heel tab featuring Nike branding.

The Nike Air Force 1 Sage Low Particle Beige W was released on October 5th, 2018 and retailed at $100.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low Shadow Beige Pale Ivory W is a sneaker that was designed for women, featuring details that give a nod to the Air Force 1 silhouette. 

The Shadow Beige Pale Ivory Nike Air Force 1 Low W features a beige suede upper with Pale Ivory and pink accents. The toe box is perforated and the upper is designed with a layered look. The midsole is made of foam that provides cushioning and support, while the rubber outsole provides traction on various surfaces.

We think that the standout feature of the Nike Air Force 1 Low Shadow Beige Pale Ivory W is its unique and eye-catching design. This shoe is designed with a double-layered upper, which creates a shadow effect and features multiple layers of stitching and overlays that add depth and dimension to the design. The Nike Air Force 1 Low Shadow Beige Pale Ivory W was released on January 1, 2020 at a suggested retail price of $110.

The Nike Air Max 95 Daisy Chain W is a fresh take on the classic Air Max silhouette. The shoe features a white mesh upper with a daisy chain graphic overlay in shades of pink, green, and yellow. The iconic Air Max cushioning system provides comfort and support, while the rubber outsole offers durability and traction. The shoe is perfect for casual wear or for adding a pop of color to your workout gear. The Nike Air Max 95 Daisy Chain W was released on August 22, 2020, and retails for $180. With its unique design and comfortable fit, this shoe is a must-have for any sneakerhead or fashion enthusiast.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III SVD Sivasdescalzo features a BEIGE/BLACK colorway, which blends ASICS' iconic Gel Lyte III silhouette with SVD Sivasdescalzo's unique design elements for a distinctive and stylish footwear offering.

The Sivasdescalzo x ASICS GEL LYTE III boasts a split tongue design for optimal fit and effortless wear, while the three densities in the midsole work in harmony to provide a smooth and responsive feel that caters to various activities. The shoe’s outsole is an embodiment of traction and durability. Crafted for traction across different surfaces, it ensures stability and confidence in every stride.

At StockX, we're captivated by the shoe’s innovative split tongue design. This distinctive feature offers an exceptional fit and effortless wear and pays homage to the model's iconic legacy. Our experts love how this element brings style and practicality, adding a unique touch to every step. The ASICS Gel Lyte III SVD Sivasdescalzo was released on the 21st of June, 2021, retailing at $179.

The Air Jordan 1 Low White Gum Hyper Pink is an Air Jordan 1 low-cut sneaker in a White/Gum/Hyper Pink colorway.

This sneaker features a Beige suede upper with tonal Swooshes contrasted by White on the laces, tongue, and the embroidered ‘Wings’ logo on the heel and Black on the sockliner and insole with Hyper Pink branding. Other details include a perforated toebox, a  tonal Jumpman logo on the tongue, and ‘23’ branding on the tongue laceholder. The upper rests on a Gum Yellow midsole and a Hyper Pink rubber outsole. 

What our experts love about this Jordan 1 Low sneaker is its unique colorway and upper construction. The Beige and White detailing on the suede upper combined with Gum Yellow and Hyper Pink accents on the sole unit make this sneaker stand out. The Air Jordan 1 Low White Gum Hyper Pink was released on April 1st, 2019, for a retail price of $90.

The New Balance 327 Light Beige W features a retro-inspired design that combines elements from New Balance's heritage 1970s running shoes. It has a design with nylon, breathable mesh, and suede upper.

This sneaker for women comes in pale blue and grey uppers. Pale blue colorways are featured on the majority of the upper part, the vamp, heel tab, overlays, and eye stays, while beige hues are dressed on the sneaker's quarter panels, and padded tongue. Its white midsole features EVA cushioning for support and comfort. To complete the sneaker’s design, its "N" logos are dressed in pale blue hues with a gum rubber outsole.

This New Balance 327 Light Beige W was released on 1st  August 2020. It retailed at $100.

The adidas ZX4000 4D Easy Mint is crafted in a Hi-Res Yellow/Linen Green/Easy Mint colorway and was released as part of the adidas ZX series. The shoe features a high-tech 4D midsole to provide stability and energy return.

The adidas ZX4000 4D Easy Mint boasts a firmly knit neon green Primeknit upper, which offers a combination of stability and support by perfectly enclosing the foot. A suede panel sits on the exterior edges the upper, while a blue Primeknit panel flanks it on the interior. The flex point is affixed by orange stitching. Meanwhile, a stiff panel that curves back away from your foot are sported on the shoe's back, while the heel reveals grey padded detailing.

What our experts think of as the best feature of the adidas ZX4000 4D Easy Mint is the suede that is resilient and resists stains. The adidas ZX4000 4D Easy Mint was released on August 22nd, 2019, at a retail price of $350.

The adidas Crazy BYW X Pharrell Gratitude and Empathy was released as part of Pharrell's mission "to make the world a better place, one shoes at a time."

Featuring messages of gratitude and equality embroidered on the tongue pull tabs of the shoes, this colorful iteration of the crazy BYW X also features a black base and green, blue, and yellow dotting colors. The adidas Crazy BYW X Pharrell Gratitude and Empathy includes a unique accessory: white/gray striped rope laces.

The adidas Crazy BYW X Pharrell Gratitude and Empathy was made available on May 31, 2018, at a retail price of $250.

Pharrell and adidas are back with another one with the release of the adidas Crazy BYW LVL X Pharrell Alternate White. This BYW LVL X Pharrell comes with a white upper plus yellow and blue accents, yellow midsole plus white and green accents, and a yellow sole plus red accents. These sneakers released in March 2019 and retailed for $250. Get groovy on the basketball court and cop these on StockX ASAP.

node.description: The Nike Air Force 1 Sage Low Black White W is a sleek and stylish sneaker that combines classic design with modern updates. The shoe features a black leather upper with white accents on the Swoosh, heel tab, and midsole. The platform sole adds a contemporary touch to the iconic silhouette, while the padded collar and insole provide comfort and support. The shoe was released on October 5, 2018, and retails for $100. The materials used in the construction of the shoe are of high quality, ensuring durability and longevity. The Nike Air Force 1 Sage Low Black White W is a must-have for sneaker enthusiasts who appreciate timeless style and modern design.

In the sneaker the adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged CBC, "CBC" stands for Celebrate Black Culture. This monochromatic shoe was designed for and released to celebrate Black History month.

The upper of the adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged CBC is lightweight Off-White PRIMEKNIT in a mixture of tighter and looser weaves. A tonal nubuck overlay on the heel, which sports embossed Ultra Boost Branding, starts at the PrimeKnit, and wraps around the synthetic leather padded collar. The laces match the PRIMEKNIT upper and cross over a nubuck tongue, which has adidas branding on the tonal tongue tag. The black insole features a Vivid Orange basketball with the CBC logo and the bright purple words "Celebrate Black Culture." The white midsole is made from Boost cushioning and the black outsole is made of Continental Rubber in a latticework pattern that allows the Boost to expand.

A detail about this sneaker that our experts love is the eyestays on the medial side, which are purple, black, and red – in contrast to the off-white eyestays on the lateral side. The adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged CBC was released on March 2nd, 2019, for a retail price of $180.

Become more lit than the firecrackers at the Lunar New Year after copping the adidas Crazy BYW Pharrell Chinese New Year (2019). This BYW comes with a red upper plus yellow accents, white midsole, and red sole. These sneakers released in January 2019 and retailed $250. Bring in the Chinese New Year dripping with swag and place a Bid on StockX today.

Love him or hate him, Kanye West is a trendsetter. Over the years, Kanye’s influence has grown tremendously and in no place is it more evident than the sneaker world. Colorways bearing any resemblance to a Kanye shoe are quickly labeled as the "Yeezy" version by the sneaker community. A perfect example of the Kanye effect is the Nike Air Max 1 FB Yeezy from 2013. Released alongside a similarly colored Roshe Run, this Nike Air Max 1 featured an upper that used a combination of black, Fresh Mint, and Pink Flash. The sneakerhead community might have labeled these Yeezys – which is better than the "Blink" nickname that first surfaced due to the black and pink combination -- but the FB in the name actually stands for futbol. Without an official connection to Kanye, these never reached the price levels of Yeezys. However, the nickname and details, like the reflective 3M Swoosh on the upper and splatter print Swoosh spread across the insoles, helped them sell quickly upon initial release and has made the Yeezy Nike Air Max 1 FB one of the most popular colorways of the FB Air Max series.

The adidas NMD R1 French Beige is a sneaker that has a neutral aesthetic. This colorway features a light, earthy beige tone on the major upper parts, including the 3-Stripes branding on the side quarter panels, while the French branding on the midsole replaces the usual adidas Trefoil logo.

The upper of the NMD R1 French Beige is crafted with a combination of mesh and suede materials, providing a combination of breathability and durability. The shoe also incorporates the iconic 3-Stripes branding on the sides, contributing to its recognizable adidas look.

What we think is the noticeable feature of this sneaker is the Boost technology in the midsole. The Boost cushioning system offers excellent energy return and responsiveness, ensuring a comfortable and cushioned step. Additionally, the shoe features EVA plugs on the midsole, delivering enhanced stability and support. The adidas NMD R1 French Beige was released on June 10th, 2016. It initially retailed at $170.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High Bio Beige Anthracite Mystic Green (W) was released as part of a series paying homage to Michael Jordan's original 1985 sneaker style.

The Beige Anthracite Mystic Green Air Jordan 1 features beige tones across its upper that is constructed from premium tumbled leather. It also comes with anthracite detailing along the toe box, side panels, heel tab, and Swoosh logo branding all set atop green outsoles complete with a herringbone tread pattern. The inside boasts textile linings combined with padded ankle collars plus air-cushioned midsoles and waxed cotton laces.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High Bio Beige Anthracite Mystic Green (W) was released on June 1st, 2019 at a retail price of $145.

The adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged Haven Triple Black all-black Primeknit upper has a reflective toebox, an upgraded cageless upper with reinforced eye stays to keep the laces secure, premium leather tongues with co-branding to match the unique adidas Consortium leather insoles, and special perforated mudguard to help you look good while surviving the upcoming wet seasons.

It has a Primeknit upper for a flexible and breathable fit, a Boost midsole for responsive cushioning and energy return, and a Stretchweb rubber outsole for enhanced traction and flexibility. Simple HAVEN branding can be seen on the left tongue, which is dressed in a "Triple Black" colorway, while the adidas logo can be seen on the right tongue.

We love the shoe's distinctive tongue and heel counter, which also has a debossed UltraBOOST label, and is made of premium leather. Reflective cotton laces decorate the pair as a last touch. This adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged Haven Triple Black was released on April 8th, 2017. This sneaker retailed at the original price of $200.

The adidas Crazy BYW 2.0 Pharrell is a collaboration between adidas and the famous musician and entrepreneur, Pharrell Williams.

The Crazy BYW 2.0 Pharrell comes in a Yellow Tint and Chalk Coral colorway with Trace Purple accents. It has a traditional lacing system that ensures a customized fit for each user. The sneaker also comes with a breathable mesh upper that offers excellent ventilation, reduces sweat, and keeps the wearer's feet cool during long hours of wear. The shoe has a fused TPU 3-Stripes branding and a suede heel patch. The outsole features a wavy pattern that helps improve traction. The collar and tongue are both padded adding to the comfort element.

Our experts say that one of the essential elements of the adidas Crazy BYW 2.0 Pharrell is its midsole. The sneaker features a Boost sole that provides exceptional cushioning. The shoe was released on March 21st, 2020, at a retail price of $180.

The adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged White Multi is a sleek and stylish running shoe that offers both comfort and performance. The shoe features a white Primeknit upper with a multi-colored pattern, providing a unique and eye-catching look. The Boost midsole provides exceptional cushioning and energy return, while the Continental rubber outsole offers excellent traction on a variety of surfaces. The shoe also features a sock-like fit for added comfort and support. Released on December 17, 2018, the adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged White Multi retails for $180. Whether you're hitting the pavement or just looking for a stylish sneaker, the adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged White Multi is a great choice.

This Nike Air Max 97 was a part of Nike Sportswear's Fall 2017 Collection for the classic silhouette. Made to commemorate the 30th Anniversary of the AM 97, this pair is known as the "Particle Beige" edition and comes in particle beige, summit white and rush pink. A premium edition, they feature a beige-based upper with pink accents. Their release date was August 4th, 2017 where they retailed for $170 in men's sizes. If you're a fan of clean toned colorways, this Air Max 97 Premium is perfect for you. Hit up the marketplace if you're looking to buy. If you have a pair and wish to sell, check what they're going for online and see if the time to move them is now.

Don't sleep on the consistent women's exclusive sneaker heat, like these Particle Beige Jordan 3s. This was the first women's edition AJ 3 to release since 2007's "Boarder Blue" colorway. Coming in particle beige, metallic red bronze and sail, they feature a suede-based upper with premium detailing. These dropped in June of 2018, where they were available at select Jordan Brand retailers worldwide and came exclusively in women's sizes, from 5-12. If you are a ride or die fan of the 3s, you need to place a Bid on these today.

The adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged White Tint lacks the traditional midfoot cage, giving it a more minimalistic and streamlined appearance.

The shoe is crafted of a breathable and lightweight Primeknit upper in a Clean White Tint colorway, providing a snug and adaptive fit while maintaining excellent airflow during runs or daily wear. The lace cage present on previous incarnations of the Ultra Boost is removed from this model, leaving simply a complete Primeknit upper. It features the adidas' renowned Boost technology in the midsole, delivering exceptional energy return and cushioning, which translates to a responsive and comfortable ride. The Stretchweb rubber outsole enhances the shoe's flexibility and grip on various surfaces.

Something noteworthy about this sneaker is a reinforced knit construction and a stabilizing Fitcounter in the heel to give support, while an elastic collar helps to ensure a tight fit. The Three-Stripes are created by thicker stitching along the midfoot in the 'White Tint' coloring, which covers the shoe in tonal shades of white and gray. The adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged White Tint debuted on November 30th, 2017, and retailed at $180.

The adidas Crazy BYW LVL X Daniel Arsham is a sneaker designed in collaboration with American artist Daniel Arsham. 

The Daniel Arsham adidas Crazy BYW LVL X has an upper that is made from a mix of suede and mesh materials, providing durability and breathability. The sneaker also has a Cotton White colorway with Collegiate Navy and bright red detailing. The midsole is made from Boost technology, providing superior cushioning and responsiveness. The outsole features a rubber material and circular patterns that provide excellent traction and durability on various surfaces.

We love the collar of the didas Crazy BYW LVL X Daniel Arsham which is made of a soft and comfortable neoprene material that wraps around the ankle. This neoprene material is designed to fit snugly around the ankle, providing a comfortable and secure fit that moves with the wearer. Additionally, the neoprene material is lined with a breathable mesh to keep the foot cool and dry while wearing the shoes. The didas Crazy BYW LVL X Daniel Arsham was released on August 11, 2018 at a retail price of $180.
